The Chinese mainland recorded 113 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Thursday, with 64 attributed to local transmissions and 49 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Friday. A total of 420 asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Thursday, and 3,336 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. The cumulative number of confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland is 227,143, with the death toll from COVID-19 standing at 5,226. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 344,088 (65,331 recoveries, 9,427 deaths) Macao: 696 (181 recoveries, five deaths) Taiwan: 4,189,929 (13,742 recoveries, 7,917 deaths)